1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:06,000
(Watch on www.kisskh.xyz Support Admin)

2
00:00:01,433 --> 00:00:02,233
Hang in there.

3
00:00:02,233 --> 00:00:03,533
We're with doctors now. You'll be fine.

4
00:00:04,400 --> 00:00:04,900
Stay strong.

5
00:00:05,433 --> 00:00:06,466
You will be fine.

6
00:00:07,333 --> 00:00:08,200
Hang in there, miss.

7
00:00:10,066 --> 00:00:13,100
[Many earlier years.]

8
00:00:20,633 --> 00:00:21,566
Take it slow, miss.

9
00:00:28,033 --> 00:00:29,433
I'm alright.

10
00:00:30,066 --> 00:00:31,000
I'm fine.

11
00:00:31,533 --> 00:00:32,833
What's happened, miss?

12
00:00:33,800 --> 00:00:35,100
How did you get stabbed?

13
00:00:39,700 --> 00:00:41,133
I was about to go home.

14
00:00:41,700 --> 00:00:43,133
Right after the boxing practice.

15
00:00:44,033 --> 00:00:47,066
Then I saw one woman was getting assaulted.

16
00:00:49,133 --> 00:00:50,533
Can't mind your own business, huh?

17
00:00:50,533 --> 00:00:51,800
So I helped her.

18
00:00:53,333 --> 00:00:54,600
They got a knife.

19
00:00:55,400 --> 00:00:56,533
And they stabbed me.

20
00:00:56,566 --> 00:00:57,266
Miss!

21
00:01:03,833 --> 00:01:05,933
I understand that you love helping people.

22
00:01:07,233 --> 00:01:09,300
But you need to be more careful.

23
00:01:10,000 --> 00:01:11,900
You still got a plenty of things to do.

24
00:01:14,466 --> 00:01:15,766
Don't risk your life for the others.

25
00:01:25,333 --> 00:01:27,333
Please let me other people a bit.

26
00:01:30,733 --> 00:01:33,766
Because it makes me wanna continue living.

27
00:03:11,700 --> 00:03:12,433
Dear.

28
00:03:14,400 --> 00:03:15,933
Got angry again?

29
00:03:16,766 --> 00:03:18,533
I can even hear your voice through the wall.

30
00:03:19,533 --> 00:03:20,400
What's going on?

31
00:03:21,466 --> 00:03:23,266
Why don't you tell me that you're coming?

32
00:03:25,300 --> 00:03:26,333
If I told you,

33
00:03:26,800 --> 00:03:29,200
will I hear little angry miss screaming?

34
00:03:31,066 --> 00:03:32,700
It's so difficult.

35
00:03:32,733 --> 00:03:36,633
I saw nothing but numbers, numbers, num... all of them.

36
00:03:37,833 --> 00:03:39,366
They gave me a headache.

37
00:03:41,133 --> 00:03:42,433
Give it a rest.

38
00:03:42,833 --> 00:03:44,733
You are a CEO's daughter.

39
00:03:44,933 --> 00:03:47,766
Are you going to do these alone? Have your underling do some.

40
00:03:48,233 --> 00:03:49,866
I'm still a newbie.

41
00:03:50,166 --> 00:03:52,166
If I do not understand every process,

42
00:03:52,633 --> 00:03:54,633
how can I teach or order anyone to do, right?

43
00:03:56,200 --> 00:03:59,466
I've been sitting for hours.

44
00:03:59,933 --> 00:04:02,833
My body is sore. It's just too hard.

45
00:04:04,333 --> 00:04:07,400
Why can't numbers are easy like music notes?

46
00:04:07,700 --> 00:04:08,733
Such a fussy.

47
00:04:10,566 --> 00:04:11,966
- And now clingy? - Yeah.

48
00:04:13,566 --> 00:04:14,500
Are you tired?

49
00:04:15,366 --> 00:04:16,400
Very much.

50
00:04:18,033 --> 00:04:19,100
I'll give you a massage.

51
00:04:19,466 --> 00:04:20,400
To help you relax.

52
00:04:25,900 --> 00:04:27,466
Can't have a little service, can you?

53
00:04:30,433 --> 00:04:31,833
- How is it? - It's so comfy.

54
00:04:33,433 --> 00:04:37,533
This hand, right? This hand, right?

55
00:04:37,766 --> 00:04:39,900
This hand, right? This hand, right?

56
00:04:40,400 --> 00:04:42,033
You're really good at this.

57
00:04:42,800 --> 00:04:44,433
You can do everything.

58
00:04:45,066 --> 00:04:48,366
How can I find another perfect girlfriend other than you?

59
00:04:49,700 --> 00:04:50,400
Hold on.

60
00:04:51,633 --> 00:04:52,500
Let's be clear.

61
00:04:54,400 --> 00:04:55,900
Why do you have to find more?

62
00:04:55,933 --> 00:04:57,600
The perfect one is sitting right here.

63
00:04:57,600 --> 00:04:58,633
Watch your words.

64
00:04:59,566 --> 00:05:01,633
I'm joking. I won't find any.

65
00:05:04,333 --> 00:05:08,066
Actually, I didn't just come here to only meet you.

66
00:05:09,900 --> 00:05:11,700
Your mother called me.

67
00:05:13,966 --> 00:05:17,166
It's about you suddenly asked me to marry you.

68
00:05:18,433 --> 00:05:20,900
We were all shocked and doesn't know what to do.

69
00:05:26,200 --> 00:05:30,666
Your mother probably thought that I want something from you.

70
00:05:34,633 --> 00:05:36,333
So do you want anything?

71
00:05:38,566 --> 00:05:39,400
Yes.

72
00:05:55,133 --> 00:05:58,133
I want to do this with you.

73
00:06:05,933 --> 00:06:07,533
Miss Weiling is ready.

74
00:06:14,033 --> 00:06:16,033
Don't get too angry or else...

75
00:06:37,733 --> 00:06:39,100
Hello, miss Weiling.

76
00:06:42,633 --> 00:06:44,000
I knew it from the start, didn't you?

77
00:06:44,766 --> 00:06:45,766
That Lalin is my daughter.

78
00:06:47,800 --> 00:06:49,366
How could I know?

79
00:06:50,133 --> 00:06:53,266
Back then, I know only Lalin whose named herself, Lyra.

80
00:06:53,900 --> 00:06:57,900
I didn't imagine myself to be this connected to you.

81
00:06:58,700 --> 00:07:00,600
Everything is just pure coincidence.

82
00:07:04,066 --> 00:07:05,566
I do not believe in the coincidence.

83
00:07:16,800 --> 00:07:18,633
I believe this is all your plan.

84
00:07:21,633 --> 00:07:23,000
I understand.

85
00:07:23,600 --> 00:07:27,000
Also our relationship had a rough start.

86
00:07:27,366 --> 00:07:29,000
But It was just a business.

87
00:07:29,633 --> 00:07:30,833
The winner takes it all.

88
00:07:31,600 --> 00:07:33,033
But about Lalin and I...

89
00:07:33,900 --> 00:07:35,533
it's really about love.

90
00:07:36,733 --> 00:07:37,366
Love?

91
00:07:38,633 --> 00:07:40,300
You? Love her?

92
00:07:40,533 --> 00:07:41,366
Really?

93
00:07:42,000 --> 00:07:43,400
Even tho you guys just met?

94
00:07:43,833 --> 00:07:45,866
Do you really know your daughter that well?

95
00:07:45,900 --> 00:07:46,800
Yes, I do.

96
00:07:47,433 --> 00:07:48,500
I am her mother.

97
00:07:48,933 --> 00:07:50,466
Because if you know Lalin well...

98
00:07:51,066 --> 00:07:55,100
you don't have to even ask me how I love her so easily.

99
00:07:56,033 --> 00:07:57,266
People like Lalin.

100
00:07:57,800 --> 00:07:59,566
They can make everyone near them happy.

101
00:07:59,900 --> 00:08:01,700
Even we only know each other for one night,

102
00:08:01,933 --> 00:08:03,133
love can still happen.

103
00:08:09,166 --> 00:08:10,466
I still believe it's too fast.

104
00:08:12,566 --> 00:08:14,666
I still want Lalin to learn more about my company.

105
00:08:16,333 --> 00:08:17,800
I can't let you marry her.

106
00:08:26,233 --> 00:08:27,666
My only daughter.

107
00:08:29,366 --> 00:08:31,266
To let her marry the one who I do not trust.

108
00:08:32,366 --> 00:08:33,100
That's a no-go.

109
00:08:36,566 --> 00:08:39,666
I totally understand your motherhood.

110
00:08:40,900 --> 00:08:45,333
Lalin must appreciate a lot about your concerning.

111
00:08:46,600 --> 00:08:48,700
But if you really know your daughter well,

112
00:08:49,433 --> 00:08:55,133
you can explain it yourself that you don't allow her to marry the one she loves.

113
00:08:56,433 --> 00:08:58,133
I believe...

114
00:08:59,066 --> 00:09:03,966
a person of your degree always got her daughter's happiness before anything else.

115
00:09:19,600 --> 00:09:21,433
Do you remember that day?

116
00:09:21,433 --> 00:09:24,466
The first time we met at the park.

117
00:09:24,733 --> 00:09:25,600
It was fun, yeah?

118
00:09:26,400 --> 00:09:28,733
Fun? It wasn't fun for me.

119
00:09:29,166 --> 00:09:31,900
You dragged me into the park at late night.

120
00:09:32,500 --> 00:09:34,066
We almost got a fine.

121
00:09:34,066 --> 00:09:37,933
We're lucky that night you ran that fast.

122
00:09:38,766 --> 00:09:40,700
You are such a little cheeky miss.

123
00:09:52,533 --> 00:09:55,833
Seeing you happy makes me happy.

124
00:09:56,833 --> 00:09:59,333
Do you like a surprise like this?

125
00:10:02,433 --> 00:10:03,700
Yes, I do.

126
00:10:04,933 --> 00:10:06,933
I like whatever you've done for me.

127
00:10:07,900 --> 00:10:10,566
Even you do the crazy dance in the middle of the road, I also like.

128
00:10:11,233 --> 00:10:12,533
You said it yourself.

129
00:10:13,633 --> 00:10:14,433
How about this?

130
00:10:14,633 --> 00:10:16,766
Don't have to get to point of dancing in the middle of the road,

131
00:10:17,066 --> 00:10:19,066
How about here? Do you dare?

132
00:10:19,566 --> 00:10:21,266
- Are you challenging me? - Yeah.

133
00:10:23,733 --> 00:10:24,600
You'll see.

134
00:10:32,833 --> 00:10:34,733
Dear, enough. It's enough.

135
00:10:34,766 --> 00:10:35,466
I believe you now.

136
00:10:37,166 --> 00:10:38,766
I still haven't finsihed the dance yet.

137
00:10:38,966 --> 00:10:40,866
I believe you that you're bold.

138
00:10:43,200 --> 00:10:45,100
You're the one who challenging me, no?

139
00:10:45,733 --> 00:10:46,800
I believe you.

140
00:10:48,433 --> 00:10:49,866
The way you are yourself,

141
00:10:50,800 --> 00:10:52,800
it's the reason why I like you since the first day we met.

142
00:10:54,566 --> 00:10:56,033
You are quite different today.

143
00:10:57,766 --> 00:11:00,700
Is this the time for official proposal?

144
00:11:01,066 --> 00:11:03,966
Have you talk with my mom? Is she alright with us?

145
00:11:04,600 --> 00:11:08,333
See? I know my mom is not that cruel.

146
00:11:13,533 --> 00:11:14,533
Lalin.

147
00:11:19,400 --> 00:11:20,866
If we cannot see each other,

148
00:11:22,166 --> 00:11:23,600
will you get sad?

149
00:11:27,733 --> 00:11:29,200
Why do you say something like that?

150
00:11:30,533 --> 00:11:31,600
Could it be...

151
00:11:33,400 --> 00:11:34,933
my mom is not okay with us?

152
00:11:48,400 --> 00:11:49,933
What did she say?

153
00:11:54,333 --> 00:11:55,233
Disagree.

154
00:11:56,533 --> 00:11:58,033
There's no way she would agree.

155
00:12:00,833 --> 00:12:03,666
I think this is getting harder than we thought.

156
00:12:08,133 --> 00:12:09,733
Are you giving up?

157
00:12:17,200 --> 00:12:18,133
I'm not giving up.

158
00:12:23,933 --> 00:12:25,166
I think...

159
00:12:27,000 --> 00:12:29,500
if we stick with the truth,

160
00:12:30,733 --> 00:12:33,000
it might hurt us less.

161
00:13:02,833 --> 00:13:06,100
I brought you here tonight.

162
00:13:07,266 --> 00:13:12,866
Just to be happy with you. Just enjoy this moment with you.

163
00:13:14,566 --> 00:13:16,466
Just in case, there will be no more.

164
00:13:48,833 --> 00:13:50,733
I want this bracelet,

165
00:13:51,500 --> 00:13:53,200
to be the reminder of me.

166
00:13:55,166 --> 00:13:57,400
In the day that we cannot be with each other.

167
00:14:15,066 --> 00:14:15,933
Dear.

168
00:14:19,533 --> 00:14:20,900
Listen to me.

169
00:14:23,366 --> 00:14:26,433
I will not let our relationship end like this.

170
00:14:29,266 --> 00:14:30,466
If it will end,

171
00:14:31,266 --> 00:14:34,533
it has to end by us not by my mom doesn't agree with.

172
00:14:40,000 --> 00:14:42,100
Trust in "us".

173
00:14:52,900 --> 00:14:54,533
I will fight for us.

174
00:16:22,833 --> 00:16:23,733
She's here, boss.

175
00:16:33,600 --> 00:16:34,733
Please sit down, miss Weiling.

176
00:16:37,266 --> 00:16:40,100
I contracted you for loaning 50 million baht.

177
00:16:40,600 --> 00:16:41,733
So what's the answer?

178
00:16:46,200 --> 00:16:48,100
My company has met with some obstacle.

179
00:16:49,066 --> 00:16:52,100
My investment plan is not going according to plan.

180
00:16:53,333 --> 00:16:54,666
But I believe,

181
00:16:54,933 --> 00:16:58,166
W Empire is going to make a big profit next year.

182
00:16:58,800 --> 00:17:00,900
I don't care much about your profit.

183
00:17:02,000 --> 00:17:04,533
The loan that you got from me last time,

184
00:17:04,900 --> 00:17:06,600
I still haven't get back any of it.

185
00:17:07,133 --> 00:17:09,066
And also,

186
00:17:09,500 --> 00:17:11,933
it passed the due date already.

187
00:17:12,533 --> 00:17:17,633
I can ensure you. If you allow me the loan this time, I can give you back the money.

188
00:17:19,133 --> 00:17:23,400
So if I let you loan the money and plus the last time you've loaned,

189
00:17:23,833 --> 00:17:25,533
the debt is going to be 100 millions baht.

190
00:17:26,133 --> 00:17:32,566
What do you have to ensure me that you will give back all my money?

191
00:17:33,800 --> 00:17:35,266
I didn't come here empty handed.

192
00:17:50,833 --> 00:17:52,066
It's up to you to accept...

193
00:17:52,766 --> 00:17:53,266
or not.

194
00:17:54,166 --> 00:17:54,966
Your choice.

195
00:18:01,200 --> 00:18:02,866
Quite an interesting statement.

196
00:18:03,366 --> 00:18:05,966
I'll say let's have a meeting next week.

197
00:18:06,200 --> 00:18:09,400
We'll prepare signed documents.

198
00:18:10,133 --> 00:18:12,266
You can just wait for the money.

199
00:18:32,040 --> 00:18:32,540
Mom!

200
00:18:33,606 --> 00:18:35,206
About Lalin and Arisa's marriage,

201
00:18:35,573 --> 00:18:36,440
you wouldn't agree, would you?

202
00:18:37,506 --> 00:18:38,706
We've talked about this already.

203
00:18:39,273 --> 00:18:39,873
I don't want to talk about it.

204
00:18:40,673 --> 00:18:42,373
I also thought about it throughly.

205
00:18:44,706 --> 00:18:47,740
If you aren't gonna let us marry, I'll go back to be Lyra.

206
00:18:49,173 --> 00:18:50,773
How well do you know her, huh?

207
00:18:52,240 --> 00:18:52,740
Arisa!

208
00:18:53,573 --> 00:18:54,440
Is this your plan?

209
00:18:55,040 --> 00:18:55,906
Don't put the blame on her.

210
00:18:56,873 --> 00:18:58,906
This is my own decision.

211
00:19:04,840 --> 00:19:05,340
Lalin.

212
00:19:06,806 --> 00:19:07,806
I think you should listen to your mother.

213
00:19:10,106 --> 00:19:12,506
Maybe it's just not a proper time.

214
00:19:13,306 --> 00:19:15,006
It's my fault for being too rush.

215
00:19:16,340 --> 00:19:17,540
So your mother doesn't trust me that much.

216
00:19:18,106 --> 00:19:19,706
My mom doesn't but I do trust you.

217
00:19:21,173 --> 00:19:22,773
I'm sure that it has to be you.

218
00:19:25,106 --> 00:19:25,606
Mom.

219
00:19:26,873 --> 00:19:28,373
I confirmed my words.

220
00:19:29,706 --> 00:19:31,506
If we can't marry, then I'll go.

221
00:19:41,106 --> 00:19:41,640
Let's go.

222
00:19:42,206 --> 00:19:43,440
Hold on, Lalin.

223
00:19:43,740 --> 00:19:44,206
Just go!

224
00:19:44,206 --> 00:19:44,706
Fine.

225
00:19:47,073 --> 00:19:47,906
Prove me wrong.

226
00:19:54,473 --> 00:19:55,540
What do you me to prove?

227
00:20:03,573 --> 00:20:04,373
Move into my house.

228
00:20:05,873 --> 00:20:06,806
So I can keep my eyes on you.

229
00:20:08,340 --> 00:20:10,073
Let me see that you're being sincere with my daughter.

230
00:20:22,840 --> 00:20:23,473
Alright.

231
00:20:28,440 --> 00:20:29,873
If that will make you trust me.

232
00:20:32,173 --> 00:20:32,873
I'll see.

233
00:21:09,273 --> 00:21:11,673
I haven't seen you smile like this for a long time.

234
00:21:13,673 --> 00:21:14,640
What do you mean?

235
00:21:16,573 --> 00:21:19,106
It seems like a real happy smile.

236
00:21:25,506 --> 00:21:27,373
It's not always like that.

237
00:21:28,673 --> 00:21:31,973
Sometimes smile cannot tell a thing.

238
00:21:33,340 --> 00:21:34,773
People can fake their smiles.

239
00:21:36,673 --> 00:21:37,206
Right.

240
00:21:39,440 --> 00:21:39,973
Now, Weiling...

241
00:21:42,673 --> 00:21:44,306
allows me to date Lalin.

242
00:21:46,806 --> 00:21:47,906
But the marriage,

243
00:21:51,306 --> 00:21:52,440
might be difficult.

244
00:21:54,506 --> 00:21:56,073
We need some time for her to trust me completely.

245
00:21:57,573 --> 00:22:00,206
You need to play the role of Lalin's lover for a while.

246
00:22:02,206 --> 00:22:03,406
I know you can do it.

247
00:22:05,573 --> 00:22:06,540
You are hard-hearted woman.

248
00:22:09,040 --> 00:22:10,006
But be careful.

249
00:22:12,606 --> 00:22:13,740
Because our own heart.

250
00:22:15,906 --> 00:22:17,040
Can become our own weakness.

251
00:22:23,806 --> 00:22:24,940
No need to worry, uncle Mek.

252
00:22:28,673 --> 00:22:30,306
I would never put my heart,

253
00:22:31,573 --> 00:22:32,773
to play in this game.

254
00:22:34,606 --> 00:22:37,373
Lalin is just a pawn in my revenge game.

255
00:22:57,006 --> 00:22:58,306
I got tea to spill, girl.

256
00:22:59,206 --> 00:23:02,173
Have you heard about Weiling's daughter that got a grand opening some time ago?

257
00:23:02,706 --> 00:23:05,540
- What's it about? - Such a drama. The thing is...

258
00:23:06,173 --> 00:23:09,540
She got a relationship with her mother's rival.

259
00:23:09,840 --> 00:23:10,773
It's just love.

260
00:23:11,206 --> 00:23:12,206
What love?

261
00:23:12,506 --> 00:23:21,240
I've heard that Weiling's finance is in trouble to the level that she has to get an illegal loan to avoid the survey.

262
00:23:23,006 --> 00:23:25,640
She got so many funds from the illegals.

263
00:23:27,740 --> 00:23:30,506
Does this mean she use her daughter to pay a debt?

264
00:23:30,840 --> 00:23:31,973
Probably.

265
00:23:40,606 --> 00:23:41,573
Excuse me.

266
00:23:42,973 --> 00:23:47,606
My parents taught me that it's better to shut up if you can't talk about anyone with positive attitude.

267
00:23:50,306 --> 00:23:51,540
Manners 101.

268
00:24:15,073 --> 00:24:15,873
Lalin!

269
00:24:17,006 --> 00:24:17,573
Dear.

270
00:24:20,173 --> 00:24:20,673
Dear.

271
00:24:33,840 --> 00:24:34,340
What's going on?

272
00:24:35,073 --> 00:24:35,840
Are you alright?

273
00:24:37,073 --> 00:24:38,673
You called me with that voice. I was so worried.

274
00:24:57,673 --> 00:24:58,440
What's going on?

275
00:25:01,106 --> 00:25:02,106
You can tell me.

276
00:25:05,406 --> 00:25:06,173
Please tell me.

277
00:25:10,206 --> 00:25:11,740
It's about my mom.

278
00:25:13,040 --> 00:25:14,573
I don't really know who to talk with.

279
00:25:15,506 --> 00:25:16,506
There's only you.

280
00:25:18,340 --> 00:25:19,340
What's with your mother?

281
00:25:19,906 --> 00:25:20,840
She's not gonna let us date?

282
00:25:21,306 --> 00:25:22,540
This time, I'll fight back.

283
00:25:23,706 --> 00:25:24,740
That's not it.

284
00:25:26,573 --> 00:25:27,906
I just heard that...

285
00:25:28,673 --> 00:25:30,473
my mom's company is going bankrupt.

286
00:25:33,640 --> 00:25:35,440
She got a lot of troubles.

287
00:25:36,273 --> 00:25:38,073
But she won't tell me anything.

288
00:25:39,706 --> 00:25:41,340
I don't know how can I help her.

289
00:25:41,873 --> 00:25:43,506
I'm also bad at doing business.

290
00:25:50,440 --> 00:25:51,173
You are bad.

291
00:25:52,106 --> 00:25:52,906
But I'm not.

292
00:25:56,240 --> 00:25:59,373
I'm willing to help you if I can.

293
00:26:00,673 --> 00:26:01,573
Don't overthink.

294
00:26:03,073 --> 00:26:06,106
But you and my mom are rivals.

295
00:26:06,640 --> 00:26:08,373
But you are my girlfriend.

296
00:26:16,440 --> 00:26:19,040
In my bad day, I still got you.

297
00:26:26,473 --> 00:26:28,073
Your mother is lucky.

298
00:26:29,106 --> 00:26:30,440
She got a daughter like you.

299
00:26:32,206 --> 00:26:33,340
That always cared for her.

300
00:26:36,206 --> 00:26:37,340
If my parents's still alive,

301
00:26:38,406 --> 00:26:39,606
Imma do the same.

302
00:26:40,406 --> 00:26:42,606
Do everything to protect them.

303
00:26:45,440 --> 00:26:46,340
Don't be scared.

304
00:26:47,640 --> 00:26:48,640
I'll help your mother.

305
00:26:53,473 --> 00:26:54,173
Thank you.

306
00:27:08,173 --> 00:27:10,140
There will be a meeting with Petra groups next month.

307
00:27:10,906 --> 00:27:13,740
They will update the interior structure a bit.

308
00:27:14,306 --> 00:27:18,273
They'll change the design, lobby and presidential suite.

309
00:27:22,273 --> 00:27:23,506
In that case, I'll let you take this job.

310
00:27:24,706 --> 00:27:25,440
I'm not into this job.

311
00:27:27,806 --> 00:27:28,540
Just can't let them catch us.

312
00:27:30,840 --> 00:27:31,340
Got it.

313
00:27:36,073 --> 00:27:37,273
Take a look at this, miss.

314
00:27:38,540 --> 00:27:39,040
What is it?

315
00:27:52,873 --> 00:27:54,040
Weiling got no choice.

316
00:27:55,040 --> 00:27:56,773
She has to get help from this woman.

317
00:28:03,240 --> 00:28:05,340
She accidentally fell into a trap like this.

318
00:28:06,706 --> 00:28:08,440
We got to make a move, Mek.

319
00:28:29,873 --> 00:28:30,773
You didn't sign.

320
00:28:32,673 --> 00:28:33,640
Is there anything wrong in the agreement?

321
00:28:35,040 --> 00:28:35,540
Not really.

322
00:28:36,073 --> 00:28:39,306
There's a rumor going around about your company is going bankrupt.

323
00:28:39,906 --> 00:28:42,740
I want to work with the company that got value.

324
00:28:43,073 --> 00:28:44,506
Not the one that is dying.

325
00:28:45,406 --> 00:28:46,840
Hope you understand, miss Weiling.

326
00:28:48,506 --> 00:28:49,040
Okay.

327
00:28:50,006 --> 00:28:50,506
So be it.

328
00:28:51,773 --> 00:28:53,106
Sometimes it's up to people's vision.

329
00:28:54,106 --> 00:28:54,873
If they can see it or not.

330
00:29:07,073 --> 00:29:07,573
Wit.

331
00:29:08,006 --> 00:29:09,640
We need to find someone who can agree to our statement fast.

332
00:29:11,206 --> 00:29:11,773
Got it, ma'am.

333
00:29:12,706 --> 00:29:13,273
But, ma'am...

334
00:29:14,906 --> 00:29:16,040
The bank told me...

335
00:29:16,873 --> 00:29:19,073
if we don't pay the first debt in time,

336
00:29:20,240 --> 00:29:21,406
you might got blacklisted.

337
00:29:22,106 --> 00:29:23,540
That's why we need to hurry.

338
00:29:24,173 --> 00:29:26,240
I won't let myself seeing my company being destroyed.

339
00:30:13,403 --> 00:30:15,269
When I was a kid, am I cute?

340
00:30:21,803 --> 00:30:22,936
Present you are cuter.

341
00:30:29,203 --> 00:30:32,636
By the way, you do look like your father.

342
00:30:34,169 --> 00:30:35,936
Many people say that.

343
00:30:37,203 --> 00:30:40,069
But I'm a loner and won't give up like my mom.

344
00:30:41,169 --> 00:30:43,236
My mom has to face a woman like her.

345
00:30:43,836 --> 00:30:45,003
That is me.

346
00:30:45,603 --> 00:30:46,336
Cheeky.

347
00:30:48,303 --> 00:30:49,169
What about you?

348
00:30:49,769 --> 00:30:51,069
Look like your mom or your dad?

349
00:30:57,236 --> 00:30:58,669
I look like both of them.

350
00:31:01,003 --> 00:31:03,403
I love art and music like my dad.

351
00:31:04,303 --> 00:31:05,636
And a loner like my mom.

352
00:31:07,469 --> 00:31:10,536
Both of them are my role model.

353
00:31:11,103 --> 00:31:13,303
I am like their perfect replica.

354
00:31:14,703 --> 00:31:15,636
I'd say,

355
00:31:16,836 --> 00:31:19,536
your parents must be so proud of you.

356
00:31:20,303 --> 00:31:21,703
I'm also proud of you.

357
00:31:23,936 --> 00:31:26,136
You are so cool.

358
00:31:27,036 --> 00:31:30,103
But you'll be much cooler if you can get along with my mom.

359
00:31:33,669 --> 00:31:35,836
I'm trying.

360
00:31:36,203 --> 00:31:38,569
But your mother has to be open minded too.

361
00:31:38,903 --> 00:31:40,536
And that's seems to be the hardest part.

362
00:31:42,836 --> 00:31:44,469
That's also my mission.

363
00:31:45,003 --> 00:31:47,503
To get you and my mom getting along.

364
00:31:50,603 --> 00:31:51,669
I won't give up.

365
00:31:58,203 --> 00:32:00,436
Here, eat up.

366
00:32:01,169 --> 00:32:02,403
It's your favourite.

367
00:32:03,269 --> 00:32:04,503
That's enough.

368
00:32:04,669 --> 00:32:07,536
You are in my house please act like a guess.

369
00:32:09,236 --> 00:32:10,269
I'm getting to the point.

370
00:32:12,403 --> 00:32:14,536
The reason I allow you to living in my house.

371
00:32:16,103 --> 00:32:17,036
I want to know you.

372
00:32:19,269 --> 00:32:20,369
I want to make sure,

373
00:32:21,269 --> 00:32:22,569
that you are sincere with my daughter.

374
00:32:27,536 --> 00:32:29,169
What do you want to know?

375
00:32:29,869 --> 00:32:30,936
Ask away.

376
00:32:31,903 --> 00:32:33,303
I have nothing to hide.

377
00:32:39,169 --> 00:32:40,436
Who's your parents?

378
00:32:41,103 --> 00:32:41,936
Where're you from?

379
00:32:48,469 --> 00:32:49,703
My parents are dead.

380
00:32:53,003 --> 00:32:54,536
Since I was 10 years old.

381
00:32:56,403 --> 00:32:58,136
I grew up with elderly relatives.

382
00:33:00,636 --> 00:33:01,636
I'm sorry.

383
00:33:06,869 --> 00:33:07,703
And...

384
00:33:08,203 --> 00:33:09,269
about property business,

385
00:33:10,636 --> 00:33:11,536
how did you get into the business?

386
00:33:12,103 --> 00:33:13,836
I always interested in this field of work.

387
00:33:14,836 --> 00:33:16,336
And I wanted to set myself up.

388
00:33:17,036 --> 00:33:18,869
So I studied in this business a lot.

389
00:33:19,803 --> 00:33:21,136
Like I said,

390
00:33:21,669 --> 00:33:24,336
You are my inspiration.

391
00:33:24,769 --> 00:33:26,169
I want to follow your footsteps.

392
00:33:26,403 --> 00:33:27,603
It's not easy.

393
00:33:29,636 --> 00:33:32,769
Before I am myself today, I've been through a lot.

394
00:33:35,003 --> 00:33:36,836
This field of work, you need to be strong.

395
00:33:38,069 --> 00:33:38,969
Need to make a right move.

396
00:33:39,369 --> 00:33:41,503
Then I need you as a mentor.

397
00:33:42,436 --> 00:33:44,269
I'm still a newbie.

398
00:33:44,669 --> 00:33:46,169
In business way.

399
00:33:47,669 --> 00:33:48,703
And in personal way.

400
00:33:50,836 --> 00:33:53,236
How did I fall in love my rival's daughter?

401
00:33:56,236 --> 00:33:57,269
What about...

402
00:33:58,436 --> 00:34:00,069
you guys stop being a rival?

403
00:34:00,403 --> 00:34:01,803
And merge our companies together.

404
00:34:02,436 --> 00:34:05,169
Both of my love ones can be together.

405
00:34:15,769 --> 00:34:16,436
Lalin.

406
00:34:18,836 --> 00:34:22,669
Stop mixing business matters and personal matters.

407
00:34:24,003 --> 00:34:25,236
They'll both screwed.

408
00:34:34,169 --> 00:34:34,803
Dear.

409
00:34:36,836 --> 00:34:37,869
Eat up.

410
00:34:38,003 --> 00:34:39,236
It's your favourite.

411
00:34:43,503 --> 00:34:44,736
You like to eat this a lot.

412
00:34:52,603 --> 00:34:53,236
Dear.

413
00:34:55,536 --> 00:34:58,203
Do you feel awkward staying here?

414
00:35:02,603 --> 00:35:03,936
I'm feeling at ease.

415
00:35:04,636 --> 00:35:06,136
I can be anywhere...

416
00:35:06,536 --> 00:35:07,569
just by your side.

417
00:35:09,903 --> 00:35:11,703
I'm serious right now.

418
00:35:11,703 --> 00:35:13,136
I ain't playing either.

419
00:35:13,269 --> 00:35:15,603
I'm upset here. I'm afraid that you might feel awkward.

420
00:35:16,203 --> 00:35:19,336
I don't know how many more conditions my mom needs.

421
00:35:20,236 --> 00:35:23,136
Even your mother got millions of conditions,

422
00:35:23,636 --> 00:35:25,003
I'll still meet her expectations.

423
00:35:26,703 --> 00:35:28,636
Because I already love her daughter.

424
00:35:33,169 --> 00:35:34,403
Alright.

425
00:35:35,203 --> 00:35:36,636
I might be overthinking.

426
00:35:38,036 --> 00:35:40,169
We'll be holding hands and go through this.

427
00:35:41,403 --> 00:35:43,069
But if you feel any uneasy,

428
00:35:43,369 --> 00:35:45,203
we can move back to your house.

429
00:35:48,903 --> 00:35:49,636
Nah.

430
00:35:51,203 --> 00:35:53,136
I'm not a person who will give up easily.

431
00:35:55,303 --> 00:35:56,936
Until I get what I want.

432
00:36:00,436 --> 00:36:01,869
And what do you want?

433
00:36:04,936 --> 00:36:05,869
Wanna know?

434
00:36:09,536 --> 00:36:11,569
The thing that I want is...

435
00:36:13,903 --> 00:36:14,769
is this!

436
00:36:15,936 --> 00:36:16,803
Dear.

437
00:36:18,269 --> 00:36:19,303
What's the kissing for?

438
00:36:19,303 --> 00:36:20,469
Smell so nice. May I take it again?

439
00:36:21,303 --> 00:36:22,603
That's enough.

440
00:36:23,236 --> 00:36:24,736
My body will get a bruise.

441
00:36:24,769 --> 00:36:26,269
What about the body? Is it nice too?

442
00:36:27,169 --> 00:36:28,436
Imma go to sleep.

443
00:36:28,636 --> 00:36:30,169
I won't let you. Come here.

444
00:36:35,503 --> 00:36:37,036
Please let me kiss.

445
00:38:41,668 --> 00:38:43,148
Is everything okay?

446
00:38:49,828 --> 00:38:51,708
I think I know even you're not telling me.

447
00:38:51,948 --> 00:38:53,428
It's something you that have to meddle with.

448
00:38:55,668 --> 00:38:57,668
I don't mean to be rude but,

449
00:38:58,468 --> 00:38:59,668
I can help you.

450
00:39:01,548 --> 00:39:02,868
Because I love Lalin.

451
00:39:04,388 --> 00:39:05,988
Lalin is stressing out no better than you.

452
00:39:09,388 --> 00:39:10,388
Does she know about this?

453
00:39:11,108 --> 00:39:11,828
She does.

454
00:39:13,948 --> 00:39:15,388
She cared about you.

455
00:39:16,268 --> 00:39:18,748
She's trying any way to help you.

456
00:39:20,188 --> 00:39:21,668
And I don't want her to suffer.

457
00:39:24,228 --> 00:39:25,308
Then how can you help me?

458
00:39:30,188 --> 00:39:31,468
What do you want?

459
00:39:32,668 --> 00:39:34,388
That's exactly what I can help you.

460
00:39:35,188 --> 00:39:36,748
But there must be a trade-off.

461
00:39:38,668 --> 00:39:39,548
What do you want in return?

462
00:39:46,268 --> 00:39:48,948
I'll help you with every loans you had.

463
00:39:49,948 --> 00:39:52,068
Including those company debts too.

464
00:39:54,428 --> 00:39:57,468
In exchange of half of your company sharing.

465
00:39:58,748 --> 00:39:59,668
Isn't it too much?

466
00:40:00,548 --> 00:40:02,028
Do you wanna take over, don't you?

467
00:40:02,468 --> 00:40:05,588
This is only way to save your company.

468
00:40:07,868 --> 00:40:12,188
Is it better to lower your ego and accept my help?

469
00:40:39,148 --> 00:40:40,468
[1 week earlier.]

470
00:40:40,508 --> 00:40:42,988
It's been so long, I thought you already forgot about me.

471
00:40:44,868 --> 00:40:48,708
How can I forget the one who made my life better to the point that I can have my own company?

472
00:40:50,388 --> 00:40:53,428
I also wouldn't dare to forget my lifesaver.

473
00:40:55,028 --> 00:40:55,708
So...

474
00:40:56,028 --> 00:40:58,708
Are you running into trouble this time?

475
00:40:59,268 --> 00:41:01,668
Or do you need more funds?

476
00:41:01,908 --> 00:41:03,948
My company is on the golden era.

477
00:41:05,268 --> 00:41:07,308
I got no problem financially.

478
00:41:07,708 --> 00:41:09,308
I only got one problem.

479
00:41:09,988 --> 00:41:10,668
A person.

480
00:41:13,268 --> 00:41:13,948
Who's it?

481
00:41:14,668 --> 00:41:16,508
The one that borrowed your money.

482
00:41:17,068 --> 00:41:17,948
Miss Weiling.

483
00:41:19,068 --> 00:41:20,068
How come?

484
00:41:20,068 --> 00:41:21,668
You got any problem with her?

485
00:41:22,268 --> 00:41:23,188
It's complicated.

486
00:41:23,508 --> 00:41:24,948
Can't tell you right now.

487
00:41:26,388 --> 00:41:27,828
May I ask you one thing?

488
00:41:28,348 --> 00:41:29,868
Please do not help her.

489
00:41:33,548 --> 00:41:34,388
You didn't sign.

490
00:41:34,588 --> 00:41:35,668
Is there anything wrong with the statement?

491
00:41:36,388 --> 00:41:38,508
Take it as my final request,

492
00:41:39,948 --> 00:41:41,468
The one who saved your life.

493
00:41:43,188 --> 00:41:45,348
After that, you own me nothing.

494
00:42:12,348 --> 00:42:13,748
That's not a little money, you know?

495
00:42:15,388 --> 00:42:16,908
I can't help you this time.

496
00:42:17,668 --> 00:42:18,868
I'll do it gently.

497
00:42:21,868 --> 00:42:23,108
Can't mind your business, can you?

498
00:42:54,748 --> 00:42:57,268
Thank you for saving my life.

499
00:42:59,148 --> 00:43:00,068
It's nothing.

500
00:43:00,868 --> 00:43:01,388
Here.

501
00:43:05,268 --> 00:43:05,908
Take it.

502
00:43:10,668 --> 00:43:11,908
If you are in any trouble,

503
00:43:12,268 --> 00:43:13,268
come find me.

504
00:43:14,268 --> 00:43:15,548
Let me repay you.

505
00:43:17,268 --> 00:43:18,788
I own you my life.

506
00:44:09,148 --> 00:44:10,868
Thank you for saving my mom.

507
00:44:17,508 --> 00:44:18,588
It's alright.

508
00:44:19,668 --> 00:44:21,948
I'll help with anything I can.

509
00:44:23,948 --> 00:44:26,828
I hope that mom will understand your sincerity.

510
00:44:35,268 --> 00:44:36,708
I didn't hope for anything.

511
00:44:37,708 --> 00:44:39,188
What's bothering you,

512
00:44:39,668 --> 00:44:41,668
it's also bothering me.

513
00:44:42,988 --> 00:44:44,828
We're about to live together.

514
00:44:45,868 --> 00:44:47,388
We have to take care of each other.

515
00:44:59,028 --> 00:45:00,148
But be careful.

516
00:45:02,028 --> 00:45:03,268
Because our own heart,

517
00:45:05,308 --> 00:45:07,068
could become our own weakness.

518
00:45:18,988 --> 00:45:21,108
The anonymous shareholder,

519
00:45:21,708 --> 00:45:23,068
Who is that?

520
00:45:23,068 --> 00:45:25,588
Aunt Yuwadee, she's my dad's sister.

521
00:45:26,508 --> 00:45:29,028
But she couldn't quite get along with my mom.

522
00:45:29,228 --> 00:45:30,468
This shareholder...

523
00:45:31,108 --> 00:45:32,388
never interferes the management.

524
00:45:32,668 --> 00:45:34,028
That's why all the decision...

525
00:45:34,788 --> 00:45:36,108
is depending on me.

526
00:45:36,468 --> 00:45:37,908
Their decision...

527
00:45:38,268 --> 00:45:40,908
will affect the direction of W Empire's management.

528
00:45:45,188 --> 00:45:47,908
I don't know what you've been t hrough in the past .

529
00:45:48,548 --> 00:45:52,868
But now, it's time to start a fresh good memory.

530
00:45:53,308 --> 00:45:56,468
I want to both laugh and cry together with you.
